<br>
Your two most important stats to raise are Charisma and Intelligence. Get those to 200 as fast as you can. INT gives you higher mana and CHA helps charm last longer and helps spells land on MoBs.<br>
<br>
Whenever grouped with a cleric or another class that can HP buff you, make sure they buff your HP up. By being the crowd controller, you are often going to have MoBs attacking you and the extra HP will be mudch needed.  If they say they can't HP buff you, give them a friendly reminder of where the mana buffs came from and also tell them that when the chanter goes down, the whole group goes down since nobody is left to control the extra MoBs.<br>
<br>
Always buff every member of your group to the fullest of your abilites as they need it. Mana buffs to all casters, speed (haste) buffs to all melees and so on. Once a group gets started it help to ask the whole group what ENC buffs are needed. Also make sure nay new people entering your group are buffed up. <br>
<br>
Also on buffing ... it helps to keep others buffed in the group on the same timer. For instance, when you cast clarity (level 29 -- breeze is level 16) on yourself, wait a few seconds before casting it on the other casters in your group. This way, when your clarity buff is fading you will know everyone else will be needing it too.  Taking this approach not only keeps your group members from having to tell you a buff is gone, but it also keeps you form having to med buffs over and over as they ware off on various members of the group.<br>
<br>
Enchanter pets suck ... bottom line.  Although they can help you some with XPing (especially at lower levels) they primarily are worthless the rest of the time.  Don't ever rely on your pet. Sure, you can wield it from time to time for a change of pace or when messing around, but don't ever think of your pet as a means of leveling. Although .. there are a few times when it can be an added tank (a weak tank at that) but you need to control it so it does not break your mezzes.<br>
<br>
ENCs are not made to solo. We are made for groups ... plain and simple. You can solo some at lower levels, but you will eventually find that it is a waste of time. You will gain experience much faster in group situattions and our arsenal of spells are much better for group situations.<br>
<br>
Know that an enchanter is an integral part of any succesful group. Any group can handle one mob, two mobs can pose a minor problem ... but three or more MoBs can mean death to the whole group UNLESS they have an enchanter to keep things under control.<br>
<br>
Learn your role, know your power and help others respect your abilities as an ENC.<br>
<br>
